HEADWORD: Invocate
<hw>In"vo*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Invocated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Invocating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>invocatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>invocare</ets>. See
<er>Invoke</er>.]</ety> <def>To invoke; to call on, or for, in
supplication; to implore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If Dagon be thy god,⟦br⟧
Go to his temple, <qex>invocate</qex> his aid.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invocation</ent>⟦br⟧
